CSS 
1. inline style : element 
2.internal style  : document / file 
3. external  : application 

Inline : Element Specific 

<p style="color:red"> Hello CSS </p>
<p style="color:red"> Hello CSS </p>
<p style="color:red"> Hello CSS </p>

     2. Internal Style : document specific
1. File.html   : Internal Style
2. File1.html : Internal Style
3. File2.html : Internal Style

How to write ? 
 <style > 
Styles will be here 
  </style>

 3.External Style Sheet :   Application specific 
           File.css 

1. File.html   : File.css
2. File1.html : File.css
3. File2.html : File.css

how to load ? 
in File.html
 <link rel="stylesheet" href="File.css"/>

This is a Common Style Sheet For complete Application .

Note : link tag is using for linking external style sheet into html file.

here href is a attribute using for reference external file.















